               <head>Javāhir al-asrār va zavāhir al-anvār by Ḥusayn ibn Ḥasan
                  al-Khvārazmī, fl. early 15th cent</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>Commentary by <persName
                     key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656318.0x000001 viaf_114789698" role="aut"
                     >Ḥusayn ibn Ḥasan al-Khvārazmī</persName> (d. 830/1426 or 840/1436) on
                     the first daftar from the <title>Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī</title> of the poet,
                     <persName key="viaf_98930150" role="ant">Jalāl al-Dīn Muḥammad Rūmī
                        Balkhī</persName>. The work appears to have been commissioned by the
                     <persName key="person_f7562" role="pat">Shah of Khvarazm</persName>,
                     <persName key="person_f7562" role="pat">Nāṣir al-Dīn Abū
                        al-Manāqib</persName>, and <persName key="person_f1545" role="pat"
                           >Prince Ibrāhīm Sulṭān</persName>, through the mediation of the
                     deceased amīr, <persName key="person_f7132" role="pat">Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn Abū
                        al-Fatḥ Shāh Malik Bahādur</persName>. </summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807"
                     n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_983-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied"
                           key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656318.0x000001 viaf_114789698">Ḥusayn ibn
                           Ḥasan al-Khvārazmī, fl. early 15th cent.</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied"
                           key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656318.0x000001 viaf_114789698">حسين ابن حسن
                           الخوارزمى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1867">Javāhir al-asrār va zavāhir
                        al-anvār</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_1867">جواهر الاسرار و زواهر الانوار</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>The work is prefixed by a detailed muqaddimah or introduction divided
                           into ten maqālah, discussing the nature of light, cosmogony, prophecy,
                           the lives of prominent Ṣūfī saints, doctrines, terminology, and
                           initiation. </p>
                        <p>Defective at the beginning. </p>
                        <p>Folio 100r left blank, marked with the phrase <q>ṣaḥīḥ al-bayāz̤</q>;
                           miscellaneous verses added later. Folio 113r left blank. Preceding folio
                           gives folio count as 113 varq. </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 301v): 4 Rabīʿ al-S̲ānī 1051/13 July 1641. Matter
                           following the colophon includes poems and medicinal recipes (ff.
                           301v-302v). </p>
                        <p>Marbled cover preserved with IOL red leather binding; net overlay on some
                           folios; wormholes and stains. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
